{"title": "Staging the Eavesdrop", "content": "Eddie: Weren't you the one I caught playin' pattycake with Old Man Acme?\n\nWhat do you do if you have information you want to spread around, but want to do it in a way where other people think they just overheard something important? Why, just say it as loudly and exaggeratedly as possible!\n\nThe reasons for this may vary. Maybe you want to Feed the Mole some false information. Maybe you want to get rid of a dangerous property by claiming that it's full of riches, thus exploiting other people's greed. Maybe you want to tell someone about something without speaking to them directly. Whatever the reasons, this is a case where one or more characters try to intentionally invoke Exact Eavesdropping on others in order to achieve some kind of goal.\n\nNot to be confused with Bluff the Eavesdropper, which is about characters noticing that they're being listened to and changing the conversation accordingly.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StagingTheEavesdrop", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/WhoFramedRogerRabbit", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/GirlsUndPanzer", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/Persona5TheDayBreakers", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/LesTuniquesBleues", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/SuskeEnWiske", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheLavenderHillMob", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Midway", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/WhoFramedRogerRabbit", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Animorphs", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/HarryPotterAndTheGobletOfFire", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/StarTrekDeepSpaceNine", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Theatre/MuchAdoAboutNothing", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/GirlGenius", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/Spacetrawler", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Gothic", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MarioAndLuigiDreamTeam", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/AvatarTheLastAirbender", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/SpongeBobSquarePants", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TheLoudHouse"], "non_media_links": [